JOHANNESBURG - Thousands of Soweto residents are set to have a bleak start to their weekend as Eskom has switched off electricity in certain parts of Dlamini. The utility said that the community was denying its workers access to the area to install prepaid meters. The utility said that it was in the process of installing these prepaid split meters throughout the Gauteng province following low payment trends that were affecting revenue. The utilityâ€™s Amanda Qithi said: "Electricity supply will not be restored until we have received confirmation that the community is willing to allow workers into the area and will not interfere with them while they do their work."